992125095936/image0.jpg?ex=69ebf354&amp;is=69eaa1d4&amp;hm=ebbbad0aa9bba8aecc63db49686300e45a665495ce8376b6e71437e904ef5eca&amp;\" alt=\"Image attachment\" title=\"Image: image0.jpg (807.48 KB)\" loading=lazy> </a></div>"], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1484515905294700625", "author": "orsib", "author_handle": "orsib", "user_id": "766598223850111037", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/766598223850111037/dfa9a5f04947e1c3995f32c568fb845d.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, March 20, 2026 7:36 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-20 7:36 a.m.", "text": "BTW. There are other things. 1. Time. Even if I set the correct time manually, after a while it falls back to UTC (most probably when it sync time from GPS or from the phone app). I'm in the CET timezone (UTC+1). 2. Vibration alert: The t-pager has a vibration motor. It would be great if I could choose in the notification menu which type of notification I'd like to use. Sound, Vibration or both. Since the motor is not really strong in the t-pager the vibration alert should be like something pulsing for 1-2 seconds.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>BTW. There are other things.\n\n1. Time. Even if I set the correct time manually, after a while it falls back to UTC (most probably when it sync time from GPS or from the phone app). I&#39;m in the CET timezone (UTC+1).\n\n2. Vibration alert: The t-pager has a vibration motor. It would be great if I could choose in the notification menu which type of notification I&#39;d like to use. Sound, Vibration or both. Since the motor is not really strong in the t-pager the vibration alert should be like something pulsing for 1-2 seconds.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}]}